        "category": "summary",
        "text": "Important: bubblewrap and flatpak security update",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "Bubblewrap (/usr/bin/bwrap) is a core execution engine for unprivileged containers that works as a setuid binary on kernels without user namespaces.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* flatpak: Access to files outside sandbox for apps using persistent= (--persist) (CVE-2024-42472)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
